loss of synchronization Check physical line and component and ethernet interface configuration
ONT Power up error ONT power up error. Either replace ONT, or disable feature via SET-NE-ALL
Remote Defect Indication from ONT Check receive signal at ONT. The OLT transmission was received with errors at the ONT
Loss of Acknowledge from ONT See if isolated for specific ONT (if not, likely a software error)
ONT has been autonomously disabled because of misbehaving transmissions and is thought to be a ROGUE ONT. This is actually a defense alarm so that the ONT doesn\A1\AFt affect the entire PON. Null
Loss of Frame at ONT 1/ Check receive signal at ONT.
Message Error Message from ONT 1/ See if isolated for specific ONT (if not, likely a software error)
Deactivate Failure of ONT 1. Reset ONT. 2. Replace ONT if Deactivate failure persists
Loss of Cell Delineation of ONT Check quality of line from ONT
Loss of PLOAM for ONT 1. Check receive signal at ONT. 2. Reset ONT. 3. If Loss of PLOAM alarm persists, replace ONT
Drift of Window. (GPON only) Check quality of line from ONT if condition persists. OLT received a transmission from the ONT at an unexpected place within the upstream virtual frame

ONT has been autonomously disabled because of misbehaving transmissions. This is actually a defense alarm so that the ONT doesn't affect the entire PON Reset ONT by administratively putting it OOS and then IS. If alarm occurs again, then ONT must likely be physically repaired or swapped
Loss of Signal at ONT (2nd highest priority for any type of ONT alarm, following INACT alarm) Check receive signal at ONT
Loss of OMCI channel for ONT. Null
Startup Failure in Ranging of ONT Re-range the ONT

Loss of Key synchronization between OLT and ONT. This key is used for the AES encryption algorithm between OLT and ONT 1. Check connectivity between OLT and ONT resulting in loss of key exchange PLOAM message between OLT and ONT. 2. Reset ONT. If condition persists, replace ONT
ONT is Inactive (1st highest priority of any type of ONT alarm) ONT needs to ranged (made active)
Physical Equipment Error of ONT Perform loopback tests
Signal Degraded for ONT Check quality of line from ONT
Received Dying Gasp indication from ONT Restore power to ONT. Dying gasp indication is due to loss of power input to ONT
ONT has been deactivated because its location on the PON has exceeded its differential reach capability. Null
Signal Fail BER threshold exceeded from ONT Check quality of line from ONT. Signal Fail BER exceeded
